Was too large for the shelf,<br />
So it stood ninety years on the floor;<br />
It was taller by half<br />
Than the old man himself,<br />
Though it weighed not a pennyweight more.<br />
It was bought on the morn<br />
Of the day that he was born,<br />
And was always his treasure and pride;<br />
But it stopped short<br />
Never to go again,<br />
When the old man died.<br /><br />

CHORUS:<br />
Ninety years without slumbering,<br />
Tick, tock, tick, tock,<br />
