Never to go again,<br />
When the old man died.<br /><br />

In watching its pendulum<br />
Swing to and fro,<br />
Many hours had he spent while a boy;<br />
And in childhood and manhood<br />
The clock seemed to know,<br />
And to share both his grief and his joy.<br />
For it struck twenty-four<br />
When he entered at the door,<br />
With a blooming and beautiful bride;<br />
But it stopped short<br />
Never to go again,<br />
When the old man died.<br />
