At the close of each week to be wound.<br />
And it kept in its place,<br />
Not a frown upon its face,<br />
And its hand never hung by its side.<br />
But it stopped short<br />
Never to go again,<br />
When the old man died.<br />
CHORUS<br /><br />

It rang an alarm<br />
In the dead of the night,<br />
An alarm that for years had been dumb;<br />
